@NODE "use" "Usage"

                                  Using ksmED
                                  -----------

                     There is not a lot to say here really.

  ALL gadgets have BubbleHelp so most of the operations can be seen that way.

       when you start ksmED it will automatically read the Kuang11 drawer
             and list any .ksm files or drawers that start with KS

         Doubleclick an item or press open to either enter a drawer or
                           start editing a .ksm file.

                            -----------------------

   the main info you will need to know is about the codes to do certain jobs

  here is the info from the Edit window help.. (taken from the KMaster.guide)


 $$1         = is replaced with the nick you input/select.
 $me         = is replaced with your nick.
 $chan       = is replaced with channel you are on.

 \\[kicknick] = is replaced with the nick you input/select.
 \\channel    = is replaced with the channel you are on.
 \\mynick     = is replaced with your nick.
 \\kick       = is replaced with /kick {nick}.
 \\bannick    = is replaced with /ban nicks-hosts.

 /me needs to be first word in a line for a action.
 /nick {nick your changing to} first word in a line.

                            -----------------------

    Pressing the right mouse button over the Editor window will open a menu
           for the main Textinput Styles like bold,inverted,underline

                            -----------------------

           To set colours you use Ctrl + C then a number from 0 to 15
       for cloured text background use a ',' char to seperate pen colour
                        from the background colour..ie.

                0,1 is white text (0) on a black background (1)

            Note: using 0 as background eg.1,0 will not show white.

                            -----------------------

          Changing the Name: string will rename the file as it saves.

                            -----------------------

        Presing The "Default Texts" text will popup a list for 1st lines

                            -----------------------

     Have a look through the .ksm files to get a better idea of the Syntax

                            -----------------------

      Also you might want to look at the KSMaster.guide ..@{"Main" link "KSMaster.guide/main"} @{"Editing & Creating" link "KSMaster.guide/data"}

@ENDNODE


@NODE "intro" "Introduction"

                                  Introduction
                                  ------------

     ksmED is a GUI for editing ALL the '.ksm' files that come with Kuang11

      If you don't have kuang then do a search on aminet and get it now :)

            For a complete List of requirements please @{" Click here " link "needs"}

            the .ksm files are data files for random messages like..

               AwayMessages , all the KSSay, KSGreets and KSKicks

      I wanted to be able to edit the files and still see what they would
     look like with AmIRC so i used my Textinput knowledge to create this.

     You can edit/create/delete/rename files and edit the data within them

               You can even change the files Version information

@ENDNODE

@NODE "needs" "Requirements"

ksmED NEEDS the following things to run...

AmIRC  http://www.vapor.com/

Kuang11 http://www.digitechmedia.net/kuang/

Textinput_mcc (distributed with AmIRC) http://www.vapor.com/

OS3.0+

@ENDNODE

@NODE "inst" "Installation"

Installation is SIMPLE :)

Just run the Install Script :)
This will also add the alias /ksmED

or..
Manual Installation:

just drag-n-drop the ksmED Program into the AmIRC drawer
This is VITAL it MUST be in the same drawer as the Kuang11 drawer

then drag-n-drop the rexx/ksmED.amirx file in AmIRC/rexx

so if your AmIRC drawr is on a disk called WEB: you will have the files.

WEB:AmIRC/ksmED
and
WEB:AmIRC/Rexx/ksmED.amirx


Then Run AmIRC

you should then load the setup gui <R_Amiga T>

to set an Alias called /ksmED use ....

ksmED = /rx ksmED"

to set an Action Button use ....
    Label: ksmED
Operation: /rx ksmED

Simple :)

@ENDNODE

@NODE "auth" "Brucey"

                               About the Author.
                               -----------------

         I have been programming on my Amiga for a couple of years now.

  Computer Languages i can write with are HTML/JS, Arexx, AmigaE, DOS, + more

               Email Address : bsteers\@ukonline.co.uk
                     WWW URL : http://web.ukonline.co.uk/bsteers/


        These are Programs i wrote that get some usage by other people..


    AmIRSay & AmiSay
    ----------------
     a speech interface for the Amigas 'Say' command
     AmIRSay is only for AmIRC
     but AmiSay can/could be used with Any Program with an ARexx port
     you are able to give names different voice styles and it has the
     ability to speak different words than are written, this is good in
     a chat room as you can speak 'oh i see' for 'oic' and so on.

     AmiSay is currently unavailable (it has a bug that i have not fixed yet)

    Clipper
    -------
     Another tool originally made for AmIRC but it has many many more uses.
     It's an MUI application using Texteditor_mcc for colours,styles,ect
     you can have unlimmited pages of unlimitted Texts then when you
     double click one the text is copied to your clipboard, then you can
     Paste it anywhere that will let you, by default Clippers settings have
     templates for HTML,AmigaGuide,AmigaE,ARexx,AWNPipe, + more


    JumpEd
    ------
     A tool for Developers, JumpEd reads through various file formats and
     builds a list of all functions/nodes, ie. for an ARexx script if the
     first word of a line ends in a colon ':' then it's a function.
     it's purpose is when you select an item in the list your editor will
     jump to the line of that function/node (Uses ARexx).

    Aminet.awnp
    -----------
     This is an AWNPipe GUI that searches Aminet or reads the RECENT file
     Allows you to Download Files or read the readme files, it's got quite
     a few features for an ARexx script and seems to work well.

                          ----------------------------
     There are many more programs i have written please goto my website to
            see them all :) http://web.ukonline.co.uk/bsteers/prog/

